ish economist and academic\n*[[1958]] &ndash; [[Kim Greist]], American actress and model\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Jennifer Hetrick]], American actress\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Andreas Petroulakis]], Greek cartoonist\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Eric Singer]], American drummer and songwriter\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Dries van Noten]], Belgian fashion designer\n*[[1959]] &ndash; [[Dave Christian]], American ice hockey player\n*  1959   &ndash; [[Ray Gillen]], American rock singer-songwriter (d. 1993)\n*  1959   &ndash; [[Ving Rhames]], American actor \n*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Lisa Martin (runner)|Lisa Martin]], Australian runner\n*[[1961]] &ndash; [[Thomas Dooley]], German-American soccer player and manager\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Billy Duffy]], English rock guitarist and songwriter ([[The Cult]])\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Bruce McCulloch]], Canadian actor and comedian\n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Emilio Estevez]], American actor\n*  1962   &ndash; [[Brett Gurewitz]], American guitarist and songwriter ([[Bad Religion]])\n*[[1963]] &ndash; [[Panagiotis Fasoulas]], Greek basketball player and politician\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Gavin Hood]], South African actor, director, producer, and screenwriter\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Stefano Modena]], Italian race car driver\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Vanessa A. Williams]], American actress and producer\n*[[1964]] &ndash; [[Pierre Morel]], French director and cinematographer\n*[[1965]] &ndash; [[Ren\u00e9e Simonsen]], Danish model and writer\n*[[1966]] &ndash; [[Stephen Baldwin]], American actor\n*  1966   &ndash; [[Dez Fafara]], American metal singer\n*  1966   &ndash; [[Bebel Gilberto]], American-Brazilian singer-songwriter\n*  1966   &ndash; [[Deborah Kara Unger]], Canadian actress\n*[[1967]] &ndash; [[Mireille Bousquet-M\u00e9lou]], French mathematician\n*  1967   &ndash; [[Bill Shorten]], Australian politician\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Tony Hawk]], American skateboarder and actor\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Catherine Tate]], English actress and screenwriter\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Suzanne Cl\u