ictoria|Sandhurst]], [[Seaford, Victoria|Seaford]] and [[Skye, Victoria|Skye]]. The [[demonym]] for a person from Frankston is a \"Frankstonian\".\n\n==Arts==\n*[[Rick Amor]] \u2013 [[painter]] and [[sculptor]]<ref name=FstonHoF2010>[http://www.frankston.vic.gov.au/Arts_Culture_and_Heritage/Frankstons_Hall_of_Fame/Hall_of_Fame_Inductees_2010/index.aspx Hall of Fame Inductees 2010] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110314185112/http://www.frankston.vic.gov.au/Arts_Culture_and_Heritage/Frankstons_Hall_of_Fame/Hall_of_Fame_Inductees_2010/index.aspx |date=14 March 2011 }}. [[City of Frankston]]. Accessed: 22 October 2010.</ref><ref name=FstonLeader4Oct10>Carlton, Donna. 4 October 2010. \"[http://frankston-leader.whereilive.com.au/news/story/recognition-for-frankstons-latest-achievers/ Hall of fame recognises Frankston's latest achievers] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706113529/http://frankston-leader.whereilive.com.au/news/story/recognition-for-frankstons-latest-achievers/ |date=6 July 2011 }}\". ''[[Leader Community Newspapers|Frankston Leader]]''. [[News Limited]]. Accessed: 22 October 2010.</ref><ref>[https://www.awm.gov.au/people/P25663/ FRick Amor]. [[Australian War Memorial]]. [[Department of Veterans' Affairs (Australia)|Department of Veterans' Affairs]] [[Government of Australia]]. Retrieved 28 August 2016</ref>\n*[[William Leslie Bowles]] \u2013 sculptor and [[medal]]list<ref>Underhill, Nancy D. H. (1979). \"Bowles, William Leslie (1885\u20131954)\". ''[[Australian Dictionary of Biography]]'' (7). [[Melbourne University Publishing|Melbourne University Press]] ([http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/bowles-william-leslie-5313 HTML version]). Accessed: 23 October 2010.</ref><ref>[https://www.awm.gov.au/people/P65019/ William Leslie Bowles]. [[Australian War Memorial]]. [[Department of Veterans' Affairs (Australia)|Department of Veterans' Affairs]] [[Government of Australia]]. Retrieved 28 August 2016</ref>\n*[[Raymond Boultwood Ewers]] 