on]] \u2013 [[boxing|boxer]], 1969 World [[Featherweight]] Champion and World Boxing Hall of Fame inductee<ref name=FstonHoF2008 /><ref name=FstonWeekly7Oct2008 /><ref name=HeraldSun30Aug09 />\n*[[Debbie Flintoff-King]], [[Order of Australia|OAM]] \u2013 [[hurdling|hurdler]], [[1982 Commonwealth Games|Brisbane 1982 Commonwealth Games]] and [[1988 Summer Olympics|Seoul 1988 Olympic Games]] gold medalist<ref name=\"FstonHoF2010\" /><ref name=\"FstonLeader4Oct10\" /><ref name=\"HeraldSun02Dec2013\" /> \n*[[Craig Mottram]] \u2013 [[Track and field|athlete]], represented Australia at three Olympic Games ([[2000 Summer Olympics|Sydney 2000]], Athens 2004, Beijing 2008)<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/mo/craig-mottram-1.html Craig Mottram]. SR/Olympic Sports. Sports Reference LLC. Accessed: 22 October 2010.</ref>\n*[[Desmond Piper]] \u2013 [[hockey]] player with the [[Australia men's national field hockey team|Australian national hockey team]] at three Olympic Games ([[1964 Summer Olympics|Tokyo 1964]], [[1968 Summer Olympics|Mexico 1968]], [[1972 Summer Olympics|Munich 1972]])<ref name=\"FstonLeader4Oct10\" /><ref name=\"FstonHoF2009\" /><ref name=\"FstonWeekley06Oct09\" /><ref name=\"FstonLeader17Oct09\" />\n*[[Natalia Rahman]] \u2013 sports shooter, Melbourne 2006 Commonwealth Games gold medalist<ref>[http://www.issf-sports.org/athletes/athlete.ashx?personissfid=SHAUSW2407198201 Natalia Rahman]. [[International Shooting Sport Federation]]. Accessed: 08 January 2014</ref>\n*[[Blake Williams|Blake 'Bilko' Williams]] \u2013 [[motocross]] rider and [[freestyle motocross]] champion<ref name=\"FstonHoF2010\" /><ref name=\"FstonLeader4Oct10\" /><ref>Jackson, Jake. 1 October 2010. \"[http://www.transmoto.com.au/fmx/news/8618842/It's-the-Frankston-Hall-of-Fame-for-Bilko It's the Frankston Hall of Fame for Bilko] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110302004038/http://www.transmoto.com.au/fmx/news/8618842/It's-the-Frankston-Hall-of-Fame-for-Bilk