away (TV series)|Getaway]]''<ref name=HeraldSun09Apr2009>[http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/sunday-heraldsun/mornington-peninsula-nepean-nepean/story-fn5bye9r-1225851827615 Mornington Peninsula - Nepean]. ''[[Herald Sun]]''. [[News Limited]]. Accessed: 22 October 2010.</ref><ref name=countryfooty>[http://www.countryfootyscores.com/the-bush-teelgraph/107-ken-piesse/562-favourite-sons-from-the-mornington-peninsula.html Favourite sons of the Mornington Peninsula]. Country Footy Scores. Accessed: 10 January 2014.</ref>\n*[[Nathan Burke]] \u2013 player with [[St Kilda Football Club]] from 1987-2003 and Captain from 1996-2000<ref name=countryfooty /><ref name=TheAge21Nov2007>[[Australian Associated Press|AAP]]. 21 November 2007. \"[http://www.theage.com.au/news/Sport/The-Saints-go-marching-to-Frankston/2007/11/21/1195321834033.html The Saints go marching to Frankston]\". ''[[The Age]]''. [[Fairfax Media]]. Accessed: 08 January 2014.</ref>\n*[[Gary Colling]] \u2013 player with St Kilda Football Club from 1968-1981 and Captain in 1978<ref name=HeraldSun09Apr2009 />\n* [[Jack Dyer]] \u2013 player known as \"Captain Blood\" with [[Richmond Football Club]] from 1931\u201349, Captain 1941-49 and Coach 1941-52, AFL Hall of Fame inductee (retired to Frankston)<ref name=\"countryfooty\" /> \n* [[Leigh Gloury]]- player with Melbourne Football Club from 1953-1954 <ref>{{Cite book|title=The Encyclopedia of AFL Footballers: every AFL/VFL player since 1897|last=Holmesby|first=Russell|publisher=BAS Publishing|year=2009|isbn=|location=|page=306|quote=|via=}}</ref>\n*[[Russell Greene]] \u2013 player with St Kilda Football Club from 1974-1979 and Hawthorn Football Club from 1980-1988, won the [[Leigh Matthews Trophy]] in 1984<ref>[http://australianfootball.com/players/player/russell%2Bgreene/10822 Russell Greene]. Australian Football. Slattery Media Group. Accessed: 10 January 2014.</ref>\n*[[Robert Harvey (footballer)|Robert Harvey]] \u2013 player with St Kilda Football Club from 1988-2008